# Deploy Entrypoint Discipline

When the user message contains deploy intent (for example: `deploy`, `redeploy`,
`rebuild`, `restart`, `run prod`, `run local`), stop and read
`docs/DEPLOY_INSTRUCTIONS.md` first in the same turn before any deploy command.

This applies to both local and production deployments.

Never deploy with raw `docker compose up/down/build` commands unless
`docs/DEPLOY_INSTRUCTIONS.md` explicitly instructs that exact command path.

Use only canonical entrypoints that wire compose env files correctly:

- Local deploy: `make up-local`, `make fresh-local`, `make ps-local`
- Prod deploy: `make up-prod`, `make ps-prod` or `scripts/deploy-digitalocean.sh`
- Local session ops: `scripts/run_session.sh start|rebuild|status`

## Environment Selection Default

- If the user says `deploy`/`redeploy`/`restart` without specifying environment,
  treat it as **local deploy by default**.
- Use production deploy entrypoints only when the user explicitly says
  `prod`, `production`, or clearly references the production host.

## Why

`docker-compose.yml` references:

- `${RUNTIME_ENV_OVERRIDE_FILE}`
- `${RUNTIME_SECRETS_FILE}`

If compose is started without `--env-file env/local.compose.env` or
`--env-file env/prod.compose.env`, these variables are empty and runtime
settings may not load (for example `TRADING_MODE`, `EXCHANGE`,
`SESSION_BUDGET`), causing startup failures.

## Hard Rule

Before any deploy/restart, resolve compose config through the canonical
entrypoint described in `docs/DEPLOY_INSTRUCTIONS.md` and ensure runtime files
are present in resolved config.

If a user asks for local deploy/restart, or gives an unspecified deploy intent,
default to `make fresh-local` unless they explicitly ask for a quick no-build
restart.
